📘 Palatiw School Supply Consolidation and Management System (PSSCMS)

A PHP-based record system designed to help Palatiw Elementary School manage student supply records, uniform sizes, grade-level data, and consolidated reporting.
Built for XAMPP (PHP + MySQL) environments.

📂 Project Structure
psscms_project/
│
├── Grade1/
├── Grade2/
├── Grade3/
├── Grade4/
├── Grade5/
├── Grade6/
│
├── add_account.php
├── admin_dashboard.php
├── consolidated_report.php
├── fix_supplies_links.py
├── fix_uniform_links.py
├── index.php
├── logout.php
├── select_grade.php
├── select_section.php
├── student_summary.php
├── supplies_summary.php
├── teacher_grade1.php
├── uniform_summary.php
│
├── palatiw_school.jpg
├── palatiw_school2.jpg
├── logo.png
│
├── config.example.php       ← safe sample config
├── database.sql             ← exported MySQL database
└── .gitignore               ← ignores sensitive files
✨ Features
📘 Manage school supply records per grade
👕 Uniform size summary & student records
📊 Consolidated school-wide reports
🧮 Grade-specific dashboards (Grade 1 – Grade 6)
🔐 Admin account creation
🗂️ Section-based selection and filtering
🖼️ Image/file linking (school logo, images, etc.)
🐍 Python utilities to repair broken data links
⚙️ Local Installation (XAMPP / Localhost)
1️⃣ Install Requirements
XAMPP (Apache + MySQL)
PHP 7.4+
MySQL / MariaDB
Browser (Chrome, Edge, etc.)
2️⃣ Place the Project Folder

Move psscms_project into:

C:\xampp\htdocs\

Access it in the browser:

http://localhost/psscms_project
3️⃣ Import the Database
Open XAMPP Control Panel
Start Apache and MySQL
Open phpMyAdmin
Create a database:
palatiw_elementary
Click Import
Select:
database.sql
Click Go

Database is now installed.

4️⃣ Configure database connection

Inside the project, duplicate:

config.example.php

Rename it to:

config.php

Edit the credentials if needed:

$host = 'localhost';
$username = 'root';
$password = '';
$database = 'palatiw_elementary';
🔐 Security Notes
DO NOT upload your real config.php to GitHub
Only upload config.example.php
.gitignore protects sensitive files
SQL file contains structure + sample records (safe)
🧩 Python Utility Scripts
File	Purpose
fix_supplies_links.py	Fixes incorrect or missing supply record links
fix_uniform_links.py	Repairs uniform-related links or filenames
📜 Usage
Open browser
Go to:
http://localhost/psscms_project
Login or navigate through grade dashboards
View or update supply/uniform records
Export or view summary reports
🛠️ Developer Notes
Uses PHP MySQLi for database connection
Organized by grade-level folders
Works on local XAMPP and production servers
Easy to modify and extend
